#. <section class="sutta" id="sn52.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "1. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Bāḷhagilānasutta → gilānasuttaṃ (bj) | bāḷhagilāyaṃ or gihīnayo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn52.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Bāḷhagilānasutta"
msgstr "10. Gravely Ill"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.10:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati andhavanasmiṃ ābādhiko "
"dukkhito bāḷhagilāno."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Dark "
"Forest. And he was sick, suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "sn52.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Anuruddha, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamenāyasmato anuruddhassa vihārena viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā "
"vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What meditation does Venerable Anuruddha practice so that physical pain "
"doesn’t occupy his mind?”"

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Catūsu kho me, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato uppannā "
"sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, I meditate with my mind firmly established in the four kinds of "
"mindfulness meditation so that physical pain doesn’t occupy my mind."

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.3"
msgid "Katamesu catūsu?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.4"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi … pe …"
msgstr "I meditate observing an aspect of the body …"

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.5"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "feelings …"

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.6"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.7"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn52.10:2.8"
msgid ""
"imesu kho me, āvuso, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato "
"uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"I meditate with my mind firmly established in these four kinds of "
"mindfulness meditation so that physical pain doesn’t occupy my mind.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.9"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.10:2.10"
msgid "Rahogatavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.303"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.1"
msgid "Rahogatena dve vuttā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.2"
msgid "sutanu kaṇḍakī tayo;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.3"
msgid "Taṇhākkhayasalaḷāgāraṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn52.10:3.4"
msgid "ambapāli ca gilānanti."
msgstr ""
